==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''cum grano salis'', literally ''with a grain of salt'', figuratively a bit of common sense (as the head was presumed filled with salt).

===Noun Phrase===
'''a grain of salt'''

# A bit of common-sensical skepticism.  Generally used in some form of ''to take with a grain of salt.''
#: ''I'd take anything I read in that paper with a grain of salt.''

